                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 4.  <span>Times between asking the question and indicating the intention to shock.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p1"></a><p>The vertical axis is the time between the participant finishing reading out the 5 words forming the question and saying “Incorrect” after the Learner did not respond, at questions 28 and 29 (the last two).</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p2" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p2"></a><p>The horizontal axis labels refer to the question number and the condition VC or HC.</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p3" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p3"></a><p>The plots are standard box plots, where the box shows the median and interquartile range, and the whiskers extend to 1.5 times the interquartile range.</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p4" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p4"></a><p>Values outside the whiskers are outliers, the single outlier shown as a cross.</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p5" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p5"></a><p>At the 28<sup>th</sup> question the time difference ranged from 8 s to 78 s with a median of 23 s for the VC (n = 19) and from 4 s to 13 s with a median of 7 s for those in the HC (n = 11).</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p6" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p6"></a><p>The Wilcoxon rank sum test rejects the hypothesis that the two samples are from the same population with P = 4.4×10<sup>−4</sup>.</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p7" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p7"></a><p>At the time of the 29<sup>th</sup> (and last) question the equivalent results are: 5–43 s with a median of 13 s for the VC (n = 16), and 5–14 s with a median of 8 s for the HC (n = 11).</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p8" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec7.fig2.caption1.p8"></a><p>Here the difference is significant with P = 0.0175.</p>
